                    <h3>Cardiology</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic">Cardiology is a branch of medicine that deals with the disorders of the heart as well as some parts of the circulatory system.</p>
                    <p>Cardiology is a specialty of internal medicine. To be a cardiologist in the United States, a three-year residency in internal medicine is followed by a three-year fellowship in cardiology.</p>
